Author::::jklsedricks
DateTime::::2016-03-07T14:55:33Z
It's more that other oils became more expensive than that palm oil got cheap. After decades of falling prices, the price of all vegetable oils soared when EU motorists were forced to buy biodiesel at whatever cost. This caused a large increase in the rate of oil palm expansion, especially on to tropical peat forest, with disastrous climate consequences as well as habitat loss. Even though vegetable oil prices have recently been falling again along with crude oil prices, they are still well above 2001 levels.



